{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HsGkzU4suUFsvinYYTi9Rt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package config\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"os\"\n     5→\t\"strconv\"\n     6→)\n     7→\n     8→type Config struct {\n     9→\tPort        string\n    10→\tDBPath      string\n    11→\tWorkerCount int\n    12→}\n    13→\n    14→func Load() Config {\n    15→\tc := Config{\n    16→\t\tPort:        \"8080\",\n    17→\t\tDBPath:      \"./miniflow.db\",\n    18→\t\tWorkerCount: 4,\n    19→\t}\n    20→\tif v := os.Getenv(\"PORT\"); v != \"\" {\n    21→\t\tc.Port = v\n    22→\t}\n    23→\tif v := os.Getenv(\"DB_PATH\"); v != \"\" {\n    24→\t\tc.DBPath = v\n    25→\t}\n    26→\tif v := os.Getenv(\"WORKER_COUNT\"); v != \"\" {\n    27→\t\tif n, err := strconv.Atoi(v); err == nil && n > 0 {\n    28→\t\t\tc.WorkerCount = n\n    29→\t\t}\n    30→\t}\n    31→\treturn c\n    32→}\n    33→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PjP1ptV6pqXyqjLTjeuXaV","session_id":"f8753322-d9f7-4d57-9d3d-95109e75f16d","uuid":"8eaf8b1a-da43-40e7-b80b-a7de63e0dfd3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PjP1ptV6pqXyqjLTjeuXaV","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of the miniflow directory structure and key components:\n\n## Miniflow Directory Structure & Key Files\n\nHere's the complete exploration of the miniflow project:\n\n### Directory Layout\n\n```\n/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/\n├── cmd/\n│   └── server/\n│       └── main.go                          # Server entry point\n├── internal/\n│   ├── activity/\n│   │   ├── builtin.go                       # Built-in activity handlers\n│   │   ├── registry.go                      # Activity type registry\n│   │   ├── worker.go                        # Activity worker pool\n│   │   └── worker_test.go\n│   ├── config/\n│   │   └── config.go                        # Configuration loader\n│   ├── executor/\n│   │   ├── executor.go                      # Workflow execution engine\n│   │   ├── scheduler.go                     # Scheduler for workflow runs\n│   │   └── executor_test.go\n│   ├── handler/\n│   │   ├── handler.go                       # HTTP request handlers\n│   │   ├── types.go                         # Request/response types\n│   │   └── handler_test.go\n│   ├── model/\n│   │   ├── workflow.go                      # Workflow & ActivitySpec definitions\n│   │   ├── run.go                           # WorkflowRun & ActivityRun definitions\n│   │   └── event.go                         # Event definition & constants\n│   └── store/\n│       ├── store.go                         # SQLite data persistence\n│       ├── errors.go                        # Store error types\n│       └── store_test.go\n├── go.mod                                   # Module definition\n├── go.sum                                   # Dependency checksums\n├── orchestra.yaml                           # Orchestra configuration\n└── server                                   # Compiled binary\n\n```\n\n---\n\n### go.mod File Contents\n\n```\nmodule miniflow\n\ngo 1.25.1\n\nrequire (\n\tgithub.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.2.5\n\tgithub.com/google/uuid v1.6.0\n\tmodernc.org/sqlite v1.46.1\n)\n```\n\n**Key Dependencies:**\n- **chi/v5**: HTTP router and middleware framework\n- **google/uuid**: UUID generation for IDs\n- **sqlite**: SQLite3 database for persistence\n\n---\n\n### Model Types\n\n#### Workflow Model (`internal/model/workflow.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ActivitySpec struct {\n\tName           string `json:\"name\"`\n\tType           string `json:\"type\"`\n\tInputExpr      string `json:\"input_expr\"`\n\tTimeoutSeconds int    `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n\tMaxRetries     int    `json:\"max_retries\"`\n}\n\ntype WorkflowDefinition struct {\n\tActivities []ActivitySpec `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n\tID         string             `json:\"id\"`\n\tName       string             `json:\"name\"`\n\tDefinition WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n\tCreatedAt  time.Time          `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Run Model (`internal/model/run.go`)\n\n```go\n// Run status constants\nconst (\n\tStatusPending   = \"pending\"\n\tStatusRunning   = \"running\"\n\tStatusCompleted = \"completed\"\n\tStatusFailed    = \"failed\"\n\tStatusCancelled = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\ntype WorkflowRun struct {\n\tID          string     `json:\"id\"`\n\tWorkflowID  string     `json:\"workflow_id\"`\n\tStatus      string     `json:\"status\"`\n\tInput       string     `json:\"input\"`\n\tOutput      string     `json:\"output\"`\n\tCurrentStep int        `json:\"current_step\"`\n\tStartedAt   *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n\tCompletedAt *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n\tCreatedAt   time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\ntype ActivityRun struct {\n\tID             string     `json:\"id\"`\n\tWorkflowRunID  string     `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n\tActivityName   string     `json:\"activity_name\"`\n\tStepIndex      int        `json:\"step_index\"`\n\tStatus         string     `json:\"status\"`\n\tInput          string     `json:\"input\"`\n\tOutput         string     `json:\"output\"`\n\tAttempts       int        `json:\"attempts\"`\n\tMaxRetries     int        `json:\"max_retries\"`\n\tTimeoutSeconds int        `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n\tStartedAt      *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n\tCompletedAt    *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n\tLastHeartbeat  *time.Time `json:\"last_heartbeat,omitempty\"`\n\tCreatedAt      time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Event Model (`internal/model/event.go`)\n\n```go\n// Event type constants\nconst (\n\tEventWorkflowStarted   = \"workflow_started\"\n\tEventWorkflowCompleted = \"workflow_completed\"\n\tEventWorkflowFailed    = \"workflow_failed\"\n\tEventWorkflowCancelled = \"workflow_cancelled\"\n\n\tEventActivityScheduled  = \"activity_scheduled\"\n\tEventActivityStarted    = \"activity_started\"\n\tEventActivityCompleted  = \"activity_completed\"\n\tEventActivityFailed     = \"activity_failed\"\n\tEventActivityRetried    = \"activity_retried\"\n\tEventActivityTimedOut   = \"activity_timed_out\"\n\tEventActivityHeartbeat  = \"activity_heartbeat\"\n)\n\ntype Event struct {\n\tID            int64     `json:\"id\"`\n\tWorkflowRunID string    `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n\tActivityRunID string    `json:\"activity_run_id,omitempty\"`\n\tEventType     string    `json:\"event_type\"`\n\tPayload       string    `json:\"payload\"`\n\tCreatedAt     time.Time `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Handler Types (`internal/handler/types.go`)\n\n```go\n// Request types\ntype CreateWorkflowRequest struct {\n\tName       string                   `json:\"name\"`\n\tDefinition model.WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n}\n\ntype StartRunRequest struct {\n\tInput string `json:\"input\"`\n}\n\n// Response types\ntype RunDetailResponse struct {\n\tmodel.WorkflowRun\n\tActivities []model.ActivityRun `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype StatsResponse struct {\n\tCounts map[string]int `json:\"counts\"`\n}\n\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n\tError string `json:\"error\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Handler Routes (`internal/handler/handler.go`)\n\nThe handler establishes routes via chi router:\n\n```go\n// Workflow Management\nPOST   /api/workflows                    # CreateWorkflow\nGET    /api/workflows                    # ListWorkflows\nGET    /api/workflows/{name}             # GetWorkflow\nPOST   /api/workflows/{name}/run         # StartRun\n\n// Run Management\nGET    /api/runs                         # ListRuns (with optional ?status= and ?limit=)\nGET    /api/runs/{id}                    # GetRun (returns RunDetailResponse with activities)\nGET    /api/runs/{id}/events             # ListEvents\nPOST   /api/runs/{id}/cancel             # CancelRun\n\n// System\nGET    /api/stats                        # Stats (returns StatsResponse)\nGET    /health                           # Health check\n```\n\n**Handler Structure:**\n- Handler holds dependencies: `*store.Store` and `*executor.Executor`\n- All endpoints use consistent JSON response format\n- Error responses use `ErrorResponse` struct with HTTP status codes\n- Request routing via `chi.URLParam()` for path parameters\n\n---\n\n### Configuration (`internal/config/config.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n\tPort        string  // Default: \"8080\"\n\tDBPath      string  // Default: \"./miniflow.db\"\n\tWorkerCount int     // Default: 4\n}\n\n// Environment variables:\n// - PORT: Server port\n// - DB_PATH: SQLite database path\n// - WORKER_COUNT: Activity worker pool size\n```\n\n---\n\n### Server Entry Point (`cmd/server/main.go`)\n\nInitialization flow:\n1. Load configuration\n2. Initialize SQLite store\n3. Create activity registry with built-in handlers\n4. Start worker pool (activity execution)\n5. Create executor and scheduler (workflow orchestration)\n6. Start HTTP server on configured port\n7. Graceful shutdown: stops scheduler, workers, then server\n\n---\n\nThis miniflow system is a lightweight workflow engine with:\n- Event-sourced persistence (events table)\n- Activity-based workflow execution\n- Configurable worker pool\n- RESTful API for workflow management and execution\n- Status tracking through multiple states (pending → running → completed/failed/cancelled)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ade9c9625815d9cb2 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 23838\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 28353</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f8753322-d9f7-4d57-9d3d-95109e75f16d","uuid":"7ad5652c-75ba-43e8-9fb3-7b281097de20","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the miniflow directory structure and key files. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory layout (all files)\n2. The go.mod file contents\n3. The model types (internal/model/*.go) - especially workflow, run, and event structs\n4. The handler types (internal/handler/types.go) - request/response types\n5. The handler routes (internal/handler/handler.go) - API route patterns\n\nThis is in /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow","agentId":"ade9c9625815d9cb2","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of the miniflow directory structure and key components:\n\n## Miniflow Directory Structure & Key Files\n\nHere's the complete exploration of the miniflow project:\n\n### Directory Layout\n\n```\n/Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow/\n├── cmd/\n│   └── server/\n│       └── main.go                          # Server entry point\n├── internal/\n│   ├── activity/\n│   │   ├── builtin.go                       # Built-in activity handlers\n│   │   ├── registry.go                      # Activity type registry\n│   │   ├── worker.go                        # Activity worker pool\n│   │   └── worker_test.go\n│   ├── config/\n│   │   └── config.go                        # Configuration loader\n│   ├── executor/\n│   │   ├── executor.go                      # Workflow execution engine\n│   │   ├── scheduler.go                     # Scheduler for workflow runs\n│   │   └── executor_test.go\n│   ├── handler/\n│   │   ├── handler.go                       # HTTP request handlers\n│   │   ├── types.go                         # Request/response types\n│   │   └── handler_test.go\n│   ├── model/\n│   │   ├── workflow.go                      # Workflow & ActivitySpec definitions\n│   │   ├── run.go                           # WorkflowRun & ActivityRun definitions\n│   │   └── event.go                         # Event definition & constants\n│   └── store/\n│       ├── store.go                         # SQLite data persistence\n│       ├── errors.go                        # Store error types\n│       └── store_test.go\n├── go.mod                                   # Module definition\n├── go.sum                                   # Dependency checksums\n├── orchestra.yaml                           # Orchestra configuration\n└── server                                   # Compiled binary\n\n```\n\n---\n\n### go.mod File Contents\n\n```\nmodule miniflow\n\ngo 1.25.1\n\nrequire (\n\tgithub.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.2.5\n\tgithub.com/google/uuid v1.6.0\n\tmodernc.org/sqlite v1.46.1\n)\n```\n\n**Key Dependencies:**\n- **chi/v5**: HTTP router and middleware framework\n- **google/uuid**: UUID generation for IDs\n- **sqlite**: SQLite3 database for persistence\n\n---\n\n### Model Types\n\n#### Workflow Model (`internal/model/workflow.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ActivitySpec struct {\n\tName           string `json:\"name\"`\n\tType           string `json:\"type\"`\n\tInputExpr      string `json:\"input_expr\"`\n\tTimeoutSeconds int    `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n\tMaxRetries     int    `json:\"max_retries\"`\n}\n\ntype WorkflowDefinition struct {\n\tActivities []ActivitySpec `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n\tID         string             `json:\"id\"`\n\tName       string             `json:\"name\"`\n\tDefinition WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n\tCreatedAt  time.Time          `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Run Model (`internal/model/run.go`)\n\n```go\n// Run status constants\nconst (\n\tStatusPending   = \"pending\"\n\tStatusRunning   = \"running\"\n\tStatusCompleted = \"completed\"\n\tStatusFailed    = \"failed\"\n\tStatusCancelled = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\ntype WorkflowRun struct {\n\tID          string     `json:\"id\"`\n\tWorkflowID  string     `json:\"workflow_id\"`\n\tStatus      string     `json:\"status\"`\n\tInput       string     `json:\"input\"`\n\tOutput      string     `json:\"output\"`\n\tCurrentStep int        `json:\"current_step\"`\n\tStartedAt   *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n\tCompletedAt *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n\tCreatedAt   time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\ntype ActivityRun struct {\n\tID             string     `json:\"id\"`\n\tWorkflowRunID  string     `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n\tActivityName   string     `json:\"activity_name\"`\n\tStepIndex      int        `json:\"step_index\"`\n\tStatus         string     `json:\"status\"`\n\tInput          string     `json:\"input\"`\n\tOutput         string     `json:\"output\"`\n\tAttempts       int        `json:\"attempts\"`\n\tMaxRetries     int        `json:\"max_retries\"`\n\tTimeoutSeconds int        `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n\tStartedAt      *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n\tCompletedAt    *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n\tLastHeartbeat  *time.Time `json:\"last_heartbeat,omitempty\"`\n\tCreatedAt      time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Event Model (`internal/model/event.go`)\n\n```go\n// Event type constants\nconst (\n\tEventWorkflowStarted   = \"workflow_started\"\n\tEventWorkflowCompleted = \"workflow_completed\"\n\tEventWorkflowFailed    = \"workflow_failed\"\n\tEventWorkflowCancelled = \"workflow_cancelled\"\n\n\tEventActivityScheduled  = \"activity_scheduled\"\n\tEventActivityStarted    = \"activity_started\"\n\tEventActivityCompleted  = \"activity_completed\"\n\tEventActivityFailed     = \"activity_failed\"\n\tEventActivityRetried    = \"activity_retried\"\n\tEventActivityTimedOut   = \"activity_timed_out\"\n\tEventActivityHeartbeat  = \"activity_heartbeat\"\n)\n\ntype Event struct {\n\tID            int64     `json:\"id\"`\n\tWorkflowRunID string    `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n\tActivityRunID string    `json:\"activity_run_id,omitempty\"`\n\tEventType     string    `json:\"event_type\"`\n\tPayload       string    `json:\"payload\"`\n\tCreatedAt     time.Time `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Handler Types (`internal/handler/types.go`)\n\n```go\n// Request types\ntype CreateWorkflowRequest struct {\n\tName       string                   `json:\"name\"`\n\tDefinition model.WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n}\n\ntype StartRunRequest struct {\n\tInput string `json:\"input\"`\n}\n\n// Response types\ntype RunDetailResponse struct {\n\tmodel.WorkflowRun\n\tActivities []model.ActivityRun `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype StatsResponse struct {\n\tCounts map[string]int `json:\"counts\"`\n}\n\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n\tError string `json:\"error\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Handler Routes (`internal/handler/handler.go`)\n\nThe handler establishes routes via chi router:\n\n```go\n// Workflow Management\nPOST   /api/workflows                    # CreateWorkflow\nGET    /api/workflows                    # ListWorkflows\nGET    /api/workflows/{name}             # GetWorkflow\nPOST   /api/workflows/{name}/run         # StartRun\n\n// Run Management\nGET    /api/runs                         # ListRuns (with optional ?status= and ?limit=)\nGET    /api/runs/{id}                    # GetRun (returns RunDetailResponse with activities)\nGET    /api/runs/{id}/events             # ListEvents\nPOST   /api/runs/{id}/cancel             # CancelRun\n\n// System\nGET    /api/stats                        # Stats (returns StatsResponse)\nGET    /health                           # Health check\n```\n\n**Handler Structure:**\n- Handler holds dependencies: `*store.Store` and `*executor.Executor`\n- All endpoints use consistent JSON response format\n- Error responses use `ErrorResponse` struct with HTTP status codes\n- Request routing via `chi.URLParam()` for path parameters\n\n---\n\n### Configuration (`internal/config/config.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n\tPort        string  // Default: \"8080\"\n\tDBPath      string  // Default: \"./miniflow.db\"\n\tWorkerCount int     // Default: 4\n}\n\n// Environment variables:\n// - PORT: Server port\n// - DB_PATH: SQLite database path\n// - WORKER_COUNT: Activity worker pool size\n```\n\n---\n\n### Server Entry Point (`cmd/server/main.go`)\n\nInitialization flow:\n1. Load configuration\n2. Initialize SQLite store\n3. Create activity registry with built-in handlers\n4. Start worker pool (activity execution)\n5. Create executor and scheduler (workflow orchestration)\n6. Start HTTP server on configured port\n7. Graceful shutdown: stops scheduler, workers, then server\n\n---\n\nThis miniflow system is a lightweight workflow engine with:\n- Event-sourced persistence (events table)\n- Activity-based workflow execution\n- Configurable worker pool\n- RESTful API for workflow management and execution\n- Status tracking through multiple states (pending → running → completed/failed/cancelled)"}],"totalDurationMs":28353,"totalTokens":23838,"totalToolUseCount":14,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1470,"cache_read_input_tokens":20164,"output_tokens":2199,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1470,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
