{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KrofQAzX6WXHeZWgoSyp5s","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013DAtGuwmNDUBaPsdohmqbv","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Client Library Engineer","prompt":"You are the Client Library Engineer for the miniflow project. You are building an HTTP client library that wraps the miniflow workflow engine API.\n\n## Technical Context\n\nTech stack:\n- Go 1.22+, standard library only (for the client — no chi or other deps)\n- net/http for API calls\n\nThe project already exists at /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow with go.mod (module name: `miniflow`).\n\nProject layout — you are adding:\n  miniflow/\n  └── internal/\n      └── client/\n          ├── client.go\n          └── client_test.go\n\nThe API you are wrapping (built by engine team, already running):\n  POST   /api/workflows              — register workflow definition (body: {\"name\":\"x\",\"definition\":{\"activities\":[...]}})\n  GET    /api/workflows              — list workflows (returns []Workflow)\n  GET    /api/workflows/{name}       — get workflow by name (returns Workflow)\n  POST   /api/workflows/{name}/run   — start run (body: {\"input\":\"...\"}) returns WorkflowRun\n  GET    /api/runs                   — list runs (query params: ?status=X&limit=N) returns []WorkflowRun\n  GET    /api/runs/{id}              — run details + activities (returns RunDetailResponse)\n  GET    /api/runs/{id}/events       — event history (returns []Event)\n  POST   /api/runs/{id}/cancel       — cancel run\n  GET    /api/stats                  — run counts by status (returns StatsResponse)\n  GET    /health                     — health check\n\n### Existing Model Types (from internal/model package — DO NOT recreate these, define your OWN response types in the client package)\n\nThe server uses these types. Your client should define its own matching types:\n\n```go\n// Workflow\ntype ActivitySpec struct {\n    Name           string `json:\"name\"`\n    Type           string `json:\"type\"`\n    InputExpr      string `json:\"input_expr\"`\n    TimeoutSeconds int    `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n    MaxRetries     int    `json:\"max_retries\"`\n}\n\ntype WorkflowDefinition struct {\n    Activities []ActivitySpec `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n    ID         string             `json:\"id\"`\n    Name       string             `json:\"name\"`\n    Definition WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n    CreatedAt  time.Time          `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\n// Run\ntype WorkflowRun struct {\n    ID          string     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowID  string     `json:\"workflow_id\"`\n    Status      string     `json:\"status\"`\n    Input       string     `json:\"input\"`\n    Output      string     `json:\"output\"`\n    CurrentStep int        `json:\"current_step\"`\n    StartedAt   *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n    CompletedAt *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt   time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\ntype ActivityRun struct {\n    ID             string     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowRunID  string     `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n    ActivityName   string     `json:\"activity_name\"`\n    StepIndex      int        `json:\"step_index\"`\n    Status         string     `json:\"status\"`\n    Input          string     `json:\"input\"`\n    Output         string     `json:\"output\"`\n    Attempts       int        `json:\"attempts\"`\n    MaxRetries     int        `json:\"max_retries\"`\n    TimeoutSeconds int        `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n    StartedAt      *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n    CompletedAt    *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n    LastHeartbeat  *time.Time `json:\"last_heartbeat,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt      time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\n// Event\ntype Event struct {\n    ID            int64     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowRunID string    `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n    ActivityRunID string    `json:\"activity_run_id,omitempty\"`\n    EventType     string    `json:\"event_type\"`\n    Payload       string    `json:\"payload\"`\n    CreatedAt     time.Time `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\n// Handler response types\ntype RunDetailResponse struct {\n    WorkflowRun           // embedded\n    Activities []ActivityRun `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype StatsResponse struct {\n    Counts map[string]int `json:\"counts\"`\n}\n\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n    Error string `json:\"error\"`\n}\n\n// Handler request types\ntype CreateWorkflowRequest struct {\n    Name       string             `json:\"name\"`\n    Definition WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n}\n\ntype StartRunRequest struct {\n    Input string `json:\"input\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Conventions\n- Client baseURL default http://localhost:8080, override via constructor param\n- All methods return typed responses and handle HTTP errors gracefully\n- Return a custom error type or wrapped errors for non-2xx responses\n\n## Your Tasks\n\n### Task 1: Implement HTTP client library with full API coverage\nCreate `internal/client/client.go` with:\n- Client struct with baseURL and http.Client\n- NewClient(baseURL string) constructor\n- Methods for every API endpoint:\n  - RegisterWorkflow(name string, definition WorkflowDefinition) (*Workflow, error)\n  - GetWorkflow(name string) (*Workflow, error)\n  - ListWorkflows() ([]Workflow, error)\n  - StartRun(workflowName string, input string) (*WorkflowRun, error)\n  - GetRun(id string) (*RunDetailResponse, error)\n  - ListRuns(status string, limit int) ([]WorkflowRun, error)\n  - GetEvents(runID string) ([]Event, error)\n  - CancelRun(id string) error\n  - Stats() (*StatsResponse, error)\n  - Health() error\n- Define all needed types in the client package (don't import internal/model)\n- Handle HTTP errors: return descriptive errors for non-2xx responses\n\nDeliverable: miniflow/internal/client/client.go\nVerify: `cd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go build ./internal/client/...`\n\n### Task 2: Write client library tests\nCreate `internal/client/client_test.go` using httptest.NewServer mocks:\n- Test each client method with mock server responses\n- Test error scenarios (500 responses, 404 responses, malformed JSON)\n- Test that correct HTTP methods and paths are used\n- Test query parameters for ListRuns\n\nDeliverable: miniflow/internal/client/client_test.go\nVerify: `cd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go test ./internal/client/... -v`\n\n## Instructions\n1. Write client.go first, build it\n2. Write client_test.go, run tests\n3. Fix any issues until both build and tests pass\n4. Report your final results","subagent_type":"general-purpose","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2549,"cache_read_input_tokens":22446,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2549},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f8753322-d9f7-4d57-9d3d-95109e75f16d","uuid":"20e69342-e9b2-454c-9483-eec27ad4d829"}
