{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KrofQAzX6WXHeZWgoSyp5s","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01H6A3Lh6CmiypjooVSkKYay","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"CLI Commands Engineer","prompt":"You are the CLI Commands Engineer for the miniflow project. You are building the CLI entrypoint with all subcommands and formatted output.\n\n## Technical Context\n\nTech stack:\n- Go 1.22+, standard library only (for the CLI)\n- net/http for API calls (via internal/client package)\n\nThe project already exists at /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow with go.mod (module name: `miniflow`).\n\nProject layout — you are adding:\n  miniflow/\n  └── cmd/\n      └── cli/\n          └── main.go\n\nIMPORTANT: Your CLI will import and use the client library at `miniflow/internal/client`. This package is being written by another teammate RIGHT NOW. You need to write your code assuming the client package exists with the types and methods described below. If the client package doesn't exist yet when you try to build, create a minimal stub so your code compiles, but the real implementation will arrive.\n\n### Client Package API (miniflow/internal/client)\n\nThe client package will provide:\n\n```go\npackage client\n\n// Types\ntype ActivitySpec struct {\n    Name           string `json:\"name\"`\n    Type           string `json:\"type\"`\n    InputExpr      string `json:\"input_expr\"`\n    TimeoutSeconds int    `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n    MaxRetries     int    `json:\"max_retries\"`\n}\n\ntype WorkflowDefinition struct {\n    Activities []ActivitySpec `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype Workflow struct {\n    ID         string             `json:\"id\"`\n    Name       string             `json:\"name\"`\n    Definition WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n    CreatedAt  time.Time          `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\ntype WorkflowRun struct {\n    ID          string     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowID  string     `json:\"workflow_id\"`\n    Status      string     `json:\"status\"`\n    Input       string     `json:\"input\"`\n    Output      string     `json:\"output\"`\n    CurrentStep int        `json:\"current_step\"`\n    StartedAt   *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n    CompletedAt *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt   time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\ntype ActivityRun struct {\n    ID             string     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowRunID  string     `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n    ActivityName   string     `json:\"activity_name\"`\n    StepIndex      int        `json:\"step_index\"`\n    Status         string     `json:\"status\"`\n    Input          string     `json:\"input\"`\n    Output         string     `json:\"output\"`\n    Attempts       int        `json:\"attempts\"`\n    MaxRetries     int        `json:\"max_retries\"`\n    TimeoutSeconds int        `json:\"timeout_seconds\"`\n    StartedAt      *time.Time `json:\"started_at,omitempty\"`\n    CompletedAt    *time.Time `json:\"completed_at,omitempty\"`\n    LastHeartbeat  *time.Time `json:\"last_heartbeat,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt      time.Time  `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\ntype Event struct {\n    ID            int64     `json:\"id\"`\n    WorkflowRunID string    `json:\"workflow_run_id\"`\n    ActivityRunID string    `json:\"activity_run_id,omitempty\"`\n    EventType     string    `json:\"event_type\"`\n    Payload       string    `json:\"payload\"`\n    CreatedAt     time.Time `json:\"created_at\"`\n}\n\ntype RunDetailResponse struct {\n    WorkflowRun\n    Activities []ActivityRun `json:\"activities\"`\n}\n\ntype StatsResponse struct {\n    Counts map[string]int `json:\"counts\"`\n}\n\ntype CreateWorkflowRequest struct {\n    Name       string             `json:\"name\"`\n    Definition WorkflowDefinition `json:\"definition\"`\n}\n\n// Client\ntype Client struct { ... }\n\nfunc NewClient(baseURL string) *Client\nfunc (c *Client) RegisterWorkflow(name string, definition WorkflowDefinition) (*Workflow, error)\nfunc (c *Client) GetWorkflow(name string) (*Workflow, error)\nfunc (c *Client) ListWorkflows() ([]Workflow, error)\nfunc (c *Client) StartRun(workflowName string, input string) (*WorkflowRun, error)\nfunc (c *Client) GetRun(id string) (*RunDetailResponse, error)\nfunc (c *Client) ListRuns(status string, limit int) ([]WorkflowRun, error)\nfunc (c *Client) GetEvents(runID string) ([]Event, error)\nfunc (c *Client) CancelRun(id string) error\nfunc (c *Client) Stats() (*StatsResponse, error)\nfunc (c *Client) Health() error\n```\n\n### CLI Commands to implement:\n\n```\nminiflow register <workflow.json>\n    → Read workflow JSON file, POST /api/workflows via client.RegisterWorkflow\n    → The JSON file contains: {\"name\":\"workflow-name\",\"definition\":{\"activities\":[...]}}\n    → Print success with workflow name\n\nminiflow run <workflow-name> [--input '{}']\n    → POST /api/workflows/{name}/run via client.StartRun\n    → Print run ID\n\nminiflow status <run-id>\n    → GET /api/runs/{id} via client.GetRun\n    → Print run info header + activity table (name, status, attempts, duration)\n\nminiflow events <run-id>\n    → GET /api/runs/{id}/events via client.GetEvents\n    → Print event timeline with timestamps\n\nminiflow list [--status X] [--limit N]\n    → GET /api/runs via client.ListRuns\n    → Print table with columns: ID (8-char prefix), Workflow, Status, Step, Age\n\nminiflow cancel <run-id>\n    → POST /api/runs/{id}/cancel via client.CancelRun\n\nminiflow workflows\n    → GET /api/workflows via client.ListWorkflows\n    → Print table of workflows\n\nminiflow stats\n    → GET /api/stats via client.Stats\n    → Print bar chart-style counts per status\n\nminiflow help\n    → Print usage information\n```\n\n### Conventions\n- Base URL: read MINIFLOW_API env var, default to http://localhost:8080\n- Human-readable output with color-coded statuses\n- Color coding: green=completed, yellow=running, red=failed, blue=pending, gray=cancelled\n- Respect NO_COLOR env var (disable colors when set)\n- Exit 1 on errors, errors to stderr\n- Events display as a vertical timeline with timestamps\n- Parse flags manually with os.Args (no flag package for subcommands, but you can use flag.NewFlagSet for individual subcommands)\n\n## Your Tasks\n\n### Task 1: Implement CLI entrypoint with all subcommands\nCreate cmd/cli/main.go with:\n- Subcommand routing via os.Args\n- All commands listed above\n- MINIFLOW_API env var for base URL\n- Error handling: print to stderr, exit 1\n\n### Task 2: Implement formatted output\nIn the same cmd/cli/main.go file, add rich output formatting:\n- Status view: run info header + activity table (name, status, attempts, duration)\n- Events timeline: vertical timeline with colored event types and timestamps\n- List table: aligned columns (ID prefix, workflow, status, step progress, age)\n- Stats: bar chart-style counts per status\n- Color coding: green=completed, yellow=running, red=failed, blue=pending, gray=cancelled\n- Respect NO_COLOR env var\n\nDeliverable: miniflow/cmd/cli/main.go\nVerify: `cd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go build ./cmd/cli`\n\n## Instructions\n1. First check if internal/client/client.go exists. If not, you'll need to wait or create a minimal stub.\n2. Write cmd/cli/main.go with all subcommands and formatted output\n3. Build it: `cd /Users/michaelhabib/dev/teams-sbx/agent-orchestra/examples/miniflow && go build ./cmd/cli`\n4. Fix any issues until the build passes\n5. Report your final results","subagent_type":"general-purpose","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2549,"cache_read_input_tokens":22446,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2549},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"cont